{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e76bfbac-a89b-4e57-9ea9-fdac5a2caf1b","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the TFM:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAlso review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9018ecbe-28a7-4b5d-a6ed-ceeb92b83937","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've already told me exactly what files need changing.","outputTokens":312,"requestId":"1428:2441A9:61722AA:6D1B1DF:69EC1B71"},"id":"13ace481-1459-4e96-8bad-a094e0ef0478","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:40:08.223Z","parentId":"31de895f-7987-41b0-bc31-bb519720e251"}
